Subject: [PATCH 0001] Probe the SPZ header version without inflating the payload

Upstream v2.1.0 exposes no way to learn a file's format version without first
inflating its gzip payload. That forces a caller to decompress attacker-controlled
data before it can decide whether the version is even supported, which is the wrong
order for an untrusted-input boundary: it hands a decompression bomb a free
expansion before any policy check runs.

This adds a bounded probe that reads the version from the gzip header region only.

Upstream status: not submitted. Upstream v3.0.0 restructures this area
(LATEST_SPZ_HEADER_VERSION), so this should be re-evaluated rather than
forward-ported blindly when the dependency is upgraded to v4 under P0-09.

Applies to: nianticlabs/spz @ 2cf0be04d86b5f9632d9073ccbbe3b1e6a609f31 (v2.1.0)

--- a/src/cc/load-spz.h
+++ b/src/cc/load-spz.h
@@ -88,6 +88,10 @@
 // Loads Gaussian splat from a byte pointer in packed format.
 GaussianCloud loadSpz(const uint8_t *data, int32_t size, const UnpackOptions &options);
 
+// Returns the packed SPZ version from a gzip header, or 0 when the input does
+// not contain a recognizable SPZ header. This does not inflate the payload.
+int32_t getSpzVersion(const uint8_t *data, int32_t size);
+
 // Saves Gaussian splat data in .ply format
 bool saveSplatToPly(
   const spz::GaussianCloud &gaussians, const PackOptions &options, const std::string &filename);
